overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, comparing its current implementation against the project's
  Statement of Work and detailed questionnaire specifications. The initial
  assessment revealed several critical omissions, such as a tiredness severity
  scale with safety warnings, specific detection for COMISA and Insufficient
  Sleep Syndrome, the absence of external resource links in reports, unweighted
  EDS scoring, incomplete CSV data export, and a lack of questions regarding
  pain and chronic fatigue. Following this review, the agent systematically
  implemented each identified gap. This involved updating data types, validation
  schemas, and UI components to incorporate the new features, including dynamic
  safety alerts for severe tiredness, detailed diagnostic logic for COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome with tailored recommendations, a dedicated section
  for external health resources, and a more robust CSV export. These
  enhancements significantly improved the questionnaire's ability to accurately
  assess sleep disorders and provide comprehensive, actionable insights.
